&lt;p&gt;You can expect a warm welcome at Milton Keynes University Hospital, our staff are friendly and welcoming. We listen to each other and work together to embed our Trusts values and behaviours.  At MKUH we appreciate our staff and reward them with an outstanding benefits package including:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Free on-site parking&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Free tea and coffee&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Great flexible working opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Discounted gym membership&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lease car scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Generous annual leave and pension scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;On site nursery (chargeable)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Extensive staff health and well-being programme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Milton Keynes University Hospital NHS Foundation Trust, in partnership with the University of Buckingham, is a University Teaching Hospital; we conduct research and teaching on site to improve the care of our patients. The hospital is undergoing significant investment, and we are proud to be rated good by the CQC. Visit our website to catch up on our latest news.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post offers an exciting opportunity to work in a developing clinical health psychology service providing specialist compassionate psychological interventions to individuals experiencing distress as a result of physical health problems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a part time post working within a small dedicated team of psychologists alongside physiotherapists, nurses and medical consultants. The post holder will working on the pain management pathway within the clinical health psychology service. This involves working with individuals and groups who are experiencing persistent pain and other significant physical health conditions. The post holder will be working in the pain management team, assessing and providing evidence-based psychology interventions. Evidence of working with people with persistent pain using evidence-based interventions is essential. Supervision is available from a senior psychologist.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To arrange an informal visit or to receive further information, please email Dr Amelie Bobsien at amelie.bobsien@nhs.net.&lt;/p&gt;
